Title: unprotectExcel
Description: Command line utility that uses COM Automation to strip password protection from an Excel file.
HomeWiki:
unprotectExcel
Command line utility that uses COM Automation to strip password protection from an Excel file. You must know the correct password for the file, and you must have Excel 2003 or later installed. MIT license (i.e. "AS IS," allowed in corporate use, no attribution, freedom, etc.)
